Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved and cored) and discard the core and seeds. Chop into
roughly 1cm pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and chopped pepper. Fry until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Once the beef is cooked, drain and discard any excess fat, then season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The beef is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g}, @Central American style spice mix{1%sachet} and
@water for the sauce{2%tbsp} to the pan. Cook, stirring to combine, ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @BBQ sauce{32%g} into the pan and mix well.

Season with salt and pepper, then remove from the heat.

Lay the @plain taco tortillas{6}(3 per person) onto a lightly oiled #baking tray{}.

Spoon the beef filling onto one half of each tortilla and top with the cheese.

Fold the other side over to make a semi-circle. Press down to keep together.

Rub each quesadilla with a little @oil{}, then bake on the top shelf of your oven
until golden, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Once ready, transfer the quesadillas to your #plates{}.

Serve the @wild rocket{20%g} on the side.

Serve the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} alongside for dipping.

Enjoy!